I should have never turned myself in.. but oh well, as long as I have my small tablet, I can work on things like KopyKate and javascript projects. Write a book, too. My GTX-1070 rig is safe at home. God knows how long I'll be in here, tough. Could be 2 days. Could be 6 months.
&nbsp;
I should do fine. I've lived in near-isolation for nearly half my life. As long as I have internet access, a quiet place and a computer, I am free.

https://www.mercurynews.com/2018/05/03/jordan-peterson-is-on-a-crusade-to-toughen-up-young-men-its-landed-him-on-our-cultural-divide-2/
&nbsp;
Seems to me that we really do need new heroes and role models in this world. It's not the 90s and 00s anymore. We may well be heading toward the most difficult period in human history.. in terms of our psychological wellbeing. Oh and that artificial intelligence thing...
&nbsp;
We all dream of space travel and robots .. but is space travel something you can Psychologically handle? Can you trust robots to always do as they're told? hm..

7_15ATNsS6aHGvBg5xoMP94sXpNaLX4fSHjN.body:
A community blacklist would make the best sense. Then again, anything that breaks the rule of freedom of speech and decentralization will encourage others to create split and alternate zeronet-like projects.
&nbsp;
I'd say, we should stay true to our roots, if we want ZeroNet to have visitors. It's up to the individual to blacklist zites they don't want to see. Otherwise, we're just reinventing the wheel.
&nbsp;
We can no longer rely on cheap tricks to make things work the way we want to .. at least on the internet. There needs to be moral pressure, and a strong community participation.. or else, you'll have 10000 different ZeroNets. We don't want that. We want one big project that will rise above all else. You can't hack your way out of this one.
